RoleDescription:
Coordinate logistics projects in an international environment with focus on SAP EWM warehouse management system. As process owner you optimize Logistics processes in our trade business and actively participate in warehouse and IT projects such as roll out of WMS systems or their integration into SAP S/4 worldwide;
Turn ideas and concepts into requirement specifications and technical designs. You validate the software quality with extended tests. You support the implementation in the production;
Identify optimization potentials in the logistics processes and IT-Systems. You will develop improvements and actively drive their implementation;
Take responsibility for tasks in the whole supply chain including testing and successful implementation in operation;
Communicate actively within our highly motivated worldwide teams and steer our external Software vendors and logistics service providers. Further you will prepare and conduct own trainings in order to support stabilization of our worldwide distribution centers;
Around 25% international travel expected. Bachelors or Masters in related business technology required (Economics, Business Engineering or Supply Chain preferred);
SAP ERP and WMS (SAP WM, EWM or other systems) experiences required. Experience with warehouse operation preferred;
Fluency in English required;
Strong analytical and problem solving skills;
Enjoy both working in teams and independently;
